1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,967
Create Hotspot Area

2
00:00:00,967 --> 00:00:03,303
First, Click “CTA Canvas” and “CTA Area Mapping”

3
00:00:03,303 --> 00:00:04,838
Click “Insert a Hotspot Area” 

4
00:00:04,838 --> 00:00:08,108
Adjust the box to the correct size and position

5
00:00:08,108 --> 00:00:09,109
Add URL to Hotspot

6
00:00:09,409 --> 00:00:11,644
Click the "URL" button from the left menu

7
00:00:11,644 --> 00:00:13,747
Enter a title name

8
00:00:13,747 --> 00:00:17,617
Enter the website URL you want to link

9
00:00:17,617 --> 00:00:18,752
Click to confirm

10
00:00:18,752 --> 00:00:22,155
Click the "preview" button on the top right

11
00:00:22,155 --> 00:00:24,124
Click hotspot area you created

12
00:00:24,124 --> 00:00:27,060
Now you can access the website you entered

13
00:00:27,060 --> 00:00:28,261
Link to Vinmobi site

14
00:00:28,261 --> 00:00:29,696
Now try to click “Select URL from VinMobi”

15
00:00:29,696 --> 00:00:32,065
Choose a VinMobi Site and Confirm

16
00:00:32,065 --> 00:00:33,400
Click the "preview" button

17
00:00:33,400 --> 00:00:35,268
Open the Preview window

18
00:00:35,268 --> 00:00:36,770
Click hotspot area you created

19
00:00:36,770 --> 00:00:38,605
Now you can access the Vinmobi site you choose

20
00:00:38,605 --> 00:00:39,939
Link to VinDesk site

21
00:00:39,939 --> 00:00:42,776
Now try to click “Select URL from VinDesk”

22
00:00:42,776 --> 00:00:45,779
Choose a VinMobi Site and Confirm

23
00:00:45,779 --> 00:00:48,748
Click the "preview" button on the top right

24
00:00:48,748 --> 00:00:51,017
Click Hotspot area you created

25
00:00:51,017 --> 00:00:53,653
Now you can access the VinDesk site you choose

26
00:00:53,653 --> 00:00:54,888
Hotspot Area Display Settings

27
00:00:54,888 --> 00:00:57,057
First, Create a hotspot area and click “Flicker” on the right

28
00:00:57,057 --> 00:00:58,358
Click to Preview

29
00:00:58,358 --> 00:01:03,263
Now you can see the area of the hotspot flickering

30
00:01:03,263 --> 00:01:04,564
OK, now we can try other display setting

31
00:01:04,564 --> 00:01:06,599
Here change to “Hover”

32
00:01:06,599 --> 00:01:08,401
Click “Preview”

33
00:01:08,401 --> 00:01:13,506
You will see the hotspot doesn't respond until you hover the mouse over it

34
00:01:13,506 --> 00:01:17,043
Here change to “Hidden”

35
00:01:17,043 --> 00:01:18,545
Click “Preview”

36
00:01:18,545 --> 00:01:22,916
This time, the hotspot doesn't respond even when you hover the mouse over it,
but you can still click the hotspot area

37
00:01:22,916 --> 00:01:24,951
Last，let's try hotspot switch method

38
00:01:24,951 --> 00:01:28,054
We use this Photo area as an example

39
00:01:28,054 --> 00:01:35,128
Copy and paste this photo

40
00:01:35,128 --> 00:01:44,471
Now, select a photo we want to switch and put in the copied photo

41
00:01:44,471 --> 00:01:46,406
From here to add this new mask as your favourite

42
00:01:46,406 --> 00:01:53,179
Add a new name, select "asset type" and confirm

43
00:01:53,179 --> 00:01:55,115
Wait until it successes

44
00:01:55,115 --> 00:01:59,619
Select "Hidden" and "Show on Hover"

45
00:01:59,619 --> 00:02:04,557
Click "Set Maker Image" and select the photo you just added

46
00:02:04,557 --> 00:02:07,994
From here, you can set the switched photo position

47
00:02:07,994 --> 00:02:11,331
Click here to preview the result

48
00:02:11,331 --> 00:02:17,904
Confirm and preview webiste

49
00:02:17,904 --> 00:02:23,776
Now you will see the hotspot area switch photo when you hover the mouse over it
